    <patterns>
      <pattern>dialog_open SSE event format: `event: dialog_open\ndata: {"codePage":"sprk_emailcomposer","fields":{"to":"...","subject":"..."},"playbookId":"..."}\n\n` — client uses this to call Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo</pattern>
      <pattern>Factory instantiation for handler: `var handler = new PlaybookOutputHandler(intentDetector, docxExport, logger)` — resolved from SprkChatAgentFactory with existing instances</pattern>
      <pattern>Autonomous execution confirmation event: `event: plan_step_complete\ndata: {"step":"dispatch","status":"completed","result":"..."}\n\n` — reuse existing plan step event type</pattern>
      <pattern>text output delegation: if OutputType="text", pass agentStream directly to CompoundIntentDetector and do not intercept — preserve existing plan_preview gate behavior</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      PlaybookDispatcher (R2-015) identifies the user's intent and extracts parameters. PlaybookOutputHandler
      (this task) decides what to DO with that match. The separation of concerns is:
      - PlaybookDispatcher: who? (which playbook, what parameters)
      - PlaybookOutputHandler: what? (how to act on the matched playbook's output type)

      The `dialog_open` SSE event is new in R2 and drives the HITL Code Page handoff pattern that is
      the centerpiece of the R2 specification. The frontend (Phase 3 Task R2-039) will handle this
      event by calling `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo` with the Code Page name and pre-populated data.

      For the autonomous path (`RequiresConfirmation=false`), the handler executes the action directly.
      For `text` output: just stream the response normally. For `download`: generate file via
      `DocxExportService`. For `insert`: emit insert content via an existing or new SSE event.
      For `navigation`: emit a navigation SSE event with the target URL/record.

      The `CompoundIntentDetector` integration is for the `text` output type only — it handles the
      case where the AI's text response is itself a multi-step plan that needs user confirmation before
      execution. Non-`text` outputs bypass `CompoundIntentDetector`.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      Strictly depends on Task R2-015 (PlaybookDispatcher and DispatchResult model must exist). Safe
      to run in parallel with R2-016, R2-017, and Group A tasks. Task R2-019 is independent. Own files:
      `Services/Ai/Chat/PlaybookOutputHandler.cs`, updates to `ChatStreamEvent` model for new event types.
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Read `CompoundIntentDetector.cs` and `DocxExportService.cs` to understand existing detection and export patterns before implementing the handler</step>
    <step order="1">Read `docs/architecture/playbook-architecture.md` to confirm JPS output node field names and how `requiresConfirmation` is stored</step>
    <step order="2">Add `dialog_open` event type to `ChatStreamEvent` discriminators (alongside existing event types from R2-010)</step>
    <step order="3">Create `PlaybookOutputHandler.cs` in `Services/Ai/Chat/` with the constructor taking `CompoundIntentDetector`, `DocxExportService`, and `ILogger`</step>
    <step order="4">Implement `HandleAsync` method with switch on `dispatch.OutputType`</step>
    <step order="5">Implement `text` branch: delegate to `CompoundIntentDetector` for plan detection; stream agent response normally</step>
    <step order="6">Implement `dialog` branch: if `RequiresConfirmation=true`, emit `dialog_open` event with Code Page name and `dispatch.ExtractedParameters` as pre-populated fields; if `false`, determine if autonomous execution is feasible for the specific action type</step>
    <step order="7">Implement `navigation` branch: emit a new `navigate` SSE event with target URL/record constructed from `dispatch.ExtractedParameters` and `ChatHostContext`</step>
    <step order="8">Implement `download` branch: call `DocxExportService` with AI-generated content; emit download link via SSE or return as regular response</step>
    <step order="9">Implement `insert` branch: emit AI-generated content via `document_stream_start/token/end` events (used by write-back in R2-023)</step>
    <step order="10">Wire `PlaybookOutputHandler` into `SprkChatAgentFactory` using factory instantiation</step>
    <step order="11">Wire `SprkChatAgent` to call `PlaybookDispatcher.DispatchAsync` and then `PlaybookOutputHandler.HandleAsync` when a dispatch match is found</step>
    <step order="12">Run `dotnet build` and verify no errors</step>
    <step order="13">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task R2-018 status to completed (🔲 → ✅)</step>
  </steps>

